      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:35:1",
      "text": [
        " قَطَعَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) فِي بَيْضَةٍ قُلْتُ وَ مَا بَيْضَةٌ قَالَ بَيْضَةٌ قِيمَتُهَا رُبُعُ دِينَارٍ وَ قُلْتُ هُوَ أَدْنَى حَدِّ السَّارِقِ فَسَكَتَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from Muhammad Bin Isa Bin Ubeyd, from Yunus, from Sama’at Bin Mahran, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> used to cut regrding a ‘<span class=\"iTxt\">Bayza</span>’. I said, ‘And what is a ‘<span class=\"iTxt\">Bayza</span>’ (a helmet)?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘A <span class=\"iTxt\">Bayza</span>, its value is a quarter Dinaar’. And I said, ‘Is it the lowest (value) for a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) of a thief?’ So he<sup>asws</sup> was silent (in agreement)’."
        ]
      }
    },
